					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85113223" rend="visible">
						<summary>Responses and letters addressed to Moses Provençal.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he">Hebrew</textLang>
						<msItem rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85113223">
							<locus from="1r" to="36v"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Responses</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">שאלות ותשובות </title>
							<note>
								<p>The contents are arranged into 5 sections: Yesode ha-Torah (begins on folio 2r), Yesode ha-Torah (folio 3v), Yesode ha-Torah (14r), Gerushin (folio 15r), Gerushin (folio 20v).</p>
								<p>The letter of enquiry in the first section was written by Reuven ben David of Perugia, dated <date calendar="Gregorian">1569</date>. The first section on Gerushin contains the letter of enquiry written by Yosef Treves of Sevilliano, dated <date calendar="Gregorian">1571</date>. Enclosed is a letter addresd by the writer to Shelomoh Kats of Mantua. The last section (on Gerushin) contains also a latter addressed by Moses Provençal to heads of talmudic academies in Jerusalem and Safed; several communications addressed to Moses Provençal by his nephew Abraham Provençal; and a letter by Barukh Aziel Haschetto (dated <date calendar="Gregorian">1554</date>), on folio 31r.</p>
								<p>On folio 36r begins a piece on rules regarding lulav and etrog, at the beginning of which the manuscript breaks off.</p>
							</note>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/45891113">Provençal, Moses ben Abraham, 1503-1575</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/45891113">פרובנצלו, משה בן אברהם</persName>
							</author>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
